<doc id="804255" wikidata="Q7362333" url="?curid=804255" title="Roman shower">
<text>A Roman shower is a type of architecturally designed shower stall that does not require a door or curtain.

These showers are often used as disabled-accessible showers in hotels. They may also be known as &quot;roll-in showers&quot;.

